Package ohos.agp.components.element

Class ShapeElement

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.agp.components.element.Element
      • ohos.agp.components.element.ShapeElement

  • public class ShapeElement
extends Element
    Provides an Element instance with a color gradient, which is usually used for component backgrounds.
    Since:
    1

    • Method Detail

      • setRingRadiusProportion

        public void setRingRadiusProportion​(float radiusProportion)
        Sets the inner radius proportion for this shape element.

        When a radius is set, the radius proportion does not take effect.

        Calling this method to change the properties will affect all shape element instances loaded from the same resource. Call makeUnique() before calling this method.

        Parameters:
        radiusProportion - Indicates the inner radius proportion to set. The default value is 3.0. The value must be positive.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - Throws this exception if the radiusProportion value is invalid.
        Since:
        7
        See Also:
        getRingRadiusProportion(), setRingRadius(int), getRingRadius(), makeUnique()

      • getRingRadiusProportion

        Since:

      • setRingRadius

        public void setRingRadius​(int radius)
        Sets the inner radius for this shape element.

        When a radius is set, the radius proportion does not take effect.

        Calling this method to change the properties will affect all shape element instances loaded from the same resource. Call makeUnique() before calling this method.

        Parameters:

      • setShape

        public void setShape​(int shape)
        Sets the shape.

        Note: be careful with the changing this property because it will affect all instances of an element loaded from the same resource. Please invoke makeUnique() before changing this property.

        Parameters:
        shape - Indicates the shape, which can be RECTANGLE, OVAL, LINE, ARC, PATH or RING.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - Throws this exception if the shape value isn't RECTANGLE, OVAL, LINE, ARC, PATH or RING.
        See Also:
        getPath(), makeUnique()

      • setShapeSize

        public void setShapeSize​(int width,
                         int height)
        Sets the size for this shape element.

        Calling this method to change the properties will affect all shape element instances loaded from the same resource. Call makeUnique() before calling this method.

        Parameters:
        width - Indicates the width of the shape element. The value must be positive or -1, which means that the shape width is the same as the container width.
        height - Indicates the height of the shape element. The value must be positive or -1, which means that the shape height is the same as the container height.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - Throws this exception if the width or height value is invalid.
        Since:
        7
        See Also:

      • setRgbColor

        public void setRgbColor​(RgbColor color)
        Sets the color for filling a ShapeElement object.

        This method does not take effect if the shape of the ShapeElement instance is LINE. Use the setRgbColors(ohos.agp.colors.RgbColor[]) method to achieve gradient effect.

        Note: be careful with the changing this property because it will affect all instances of an element loaded from the same resource. Please invoke makeUnique() before changing this property.

        Parameters:
        color - Indicates the color value. The value null means transparent color.
        Since:
        3
        See Also:
        setRgbColors(RgbColor[]), getRgbColors(), makeUnique(), RgbPalette

      • setRgbColors

        public void setRgbColors​(RgbColor[] colors)
        Sets the colors for filling a ShapeElement object with gradient effect.

        This method does not take effect if the shape of the ShapeElement object is LINE. You can call setRgbColor(ohos.agp.colors.RgbColor) to apply a single color to a ShapeElement object.

        Note: For set this property in XML use attribute ohos:colors with next inner parameters: 1.#AARRGGBB - RgbColor in hex type. For example: ohos:colors = "#FFFFFFFF" 2.#RRGGBB - RgbColor in hex type where alpha for color will 0xFF. For example: ohos:colors = "#FFFFFF" 3.name_of_color - value from RgbPalette. For example: ohos:colors = "red, green, blue" 4.color:name_of_color - multiple color from user json file in resource where color: indicates that the color is in the resources and name_of_color is name of color in user json file. For example: 

        
     <shape>
         <solid ohos:colors="color:dark_violet, green, #FF0000FF, ..., color:canary_yellow"/>
      </shape>
        Note: If write incorrect color program throw IllegalArgumentException

        Note: be careful with the changing this property because it will affect all instances of an element loaded from the same resource. Please invoke makeUnique() before changing this property.

        Parameters:
        colors - Indicates the colors for filling the shape element object.
        Since:
        3
        See Also:
        setRgbColor(RgbColor), getRgbColors(), makeUnique(), RgbPalette

      • setStroke

        public void setStroke​(int width,
                      RgbColor color,
                      float dashSize,
                      float dashSpace)
        Sets the stroke width and color with dashes for this shape element.

        The dash usage is equivalent to setDashPathEffectValues(float[],float) with the dash path effect intervals (specified by dashSize and dashSpace) and the phase 0 as input parameters.

        Calling this method to change the properties will affect all shape element instances loaded from the same resource. Call makeUnique() before calling this method.

        Parameters:
        width - Indicates the stroke width to set. The value must be positive or 0. No stroke is drawn when the value is 0. Nothing happens when an invalid value is passed.
        color - Indicates the stroke color to set. A transparent stroke is drawn when the value is null.
        dashSize - Indicates the length of each dash, in pixels. The value must be positive or 0. No dash is drawn when the value is 0 or negative.
        dashSpace - Indicates the gap between two adjacent dashes, in pixels. The value must be positive. No dash is drawn when the value is 0 or negative.
        Since:
        7
        See Also:
        setStroke(int, RgbColor), setStroke(int, RgbColor[]), setStroke(int, RgbColor[], float, float), setStrokeCap(Paint.StrokeCap), getStrokeColors(), getStrokeWidth(), setDashPathEffectValues(float[], float), makeUnique()
